    "Global population growth, increasing wealth, and urbanization, particularly in Asia and Africa, create changes in global consumption patterns, lifestyles and food preferences, leading to an increase in animal protein demands (Smith & Barnes, 2015; Van Huis, 2013).",
    "This will affect the demand for livestock feed and inevitably place heavy pressure on already limited resources (Van Huis, 2013).",
    "Additionally, this will have an effect on the demand for animal feed and inevitably put a significant strain on already scarce resources (Van Huis, 2013).",
    "Protein shortages are caused by the rising demand, hence alternate sources of sustainable protein are required (Halloran et al., 2016; Van Huis et al., 2015).",
    "The cost of feed, including replacements like fishmeal and soybean meal, which accounts for 60-70% of production expenses, is one of the main restrictions (Vantomme et al., 2012)."
  ],
